---
import BaseLayout from "@layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="AI-Assisted Content Policy | Coloring Atlas" description="How Coloring Atlas uses AI-assisted image drafting, human review, cleanup, and print formatting." canonicalPath="/en/ai-assisted-content-policy/">
  <section class="section trust-page">
    <p class="eyebrow">Trust</p>
    <h1>AI-assisted content policy</h1>
    <p class="lead">Some printable pages are created with digital illustration tools, AI-assisted drafting, and human review. Each file should be checked, cleaned, formatted, and prepared for printing before publication.</p>
    <div class="panel guide">
      <h2>Quality and rights review</h2>
      <p>The publishing workflow should avoid unlicensed copyrighted characters, brand logos, trademarked costumes, celebrity likenesses, and confusingly similar franchise material.</p>
      <p>Files should be reviewed for clean line art, printable margins, broken AI artifacts, correct metadata, and working PDF downloads.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .trust-page {
    max-width: 920px;
  }

  .guide {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.8rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    padding: 1.1rem;
  }
</style>
